caption: I have been going to this store for a long time and they always have fresh sushi here. The staff are friendly most times and they try their best to make sure customers have a good experience. It's a very cozy and inviting place. After a few years I have found they put alcohol or rice wine in their sushi rice so it is not halal

The very first time I ordered here the food was very delicious. I got General Tao chicken with Hibachi Fried rice and it hit the spot. Unfortunately, the second time wasn’t as pleasant. I ordered chicken hibachi with noodles and it was awful. I felt very offended because I spent $47.73 for food that a dog wouldn’t eat. There was so much water at the bottom of the dish that I could’ve used it to quench my thirst. The noodles looked similar instant noodles. If I wanted instant noodles, I would’ve gone to the bodega to pick some up. On top of everything, the order came TWO HOURS late from Uber Eats. My stomach is in shambles now. Thanks.

I ordered delivery via Grubhub which came super quickly. The food was delicious! Packages perfectly for take out. I didn't even need to use much soy sauce on the food because the sauce the food was made in was so good and plentiful. I chose a salad since I knew the food would be traveling, and everything was SO good! One somewhat odd thing was one of us got mushrooms in the veggies while I didn't (which was good for me because I don't like them) but it was funny. Very good and would definitely order again. Prices were also great for the portions and quality.

I love the dishes offered here. It's so hard to find an Asian restaurant that offers multiple Asian cuisines like Chinese, Thai, Japanese, Malaysian and Singaporean in one menu. They excel in flavor and authenticity too. One of the rarer places in Brooklyn to get my craving for Thai noodles. The delivery man is fast, I've never experienced a late delivery. This is really one of the few Chinese owned restaurants that wants to please its customers with a great experience. The food tastes great, wide assortment, fast delivery, competitive prices, friendly staff and positive reviews.

My first impression or visual when I heard about this restaurant was the famous "Patron" tequila. I thought this may be a training ground for people to get ready for the "Patron Challenge" Well, one thing is for sure, El Patron in my book stands for Inexpensive and tasty Mexican food. The Lunch specials are a great deal!  Here's a tip - Yelp check in = free slice of flan! already off to a great start! I was here for lunch and the deals are excellent in my book. Delicious copious amounts of food with great service thrown in!  We started out by ordering "Flautas" a fried tortilla almost resembles a crispy egg roll filled with chicken and topped with pico de gallo, lettuce and sour cream. The chicken meat was a little under seasoned for my taste, but it was still a great appetizer to start the meal.  For our Entrée we ordered the Mini Bandeja paisa and Combo Patron. We were served a side salad before our meals arrived. We were amazed how large the lunch orders were. The Bandeja looked like a thing of beauty when they placed it on our table, perfectly cooked medium skirt steak, egg sunny side up, moist avocado, sweet moist plantains and pork belly fried up nice, crispy and crunchy. The white rice was moist and not overly salty. The beans were soft, flavorful and OMG delicious!  The Combo Patron was a huge plate of Awesomeness! The combo comes with a Steak taco, pork tostada and Chicken enchilada. They serve It with yellow rice and beans, The combo looked like a big mess, messy to eat but our taste buds savored every delicious bite!  We were so full from our meals and had leftovers to take home, but for some strange reason we always find room for dessert, a free one in this case, thanks Yelp! :) The Flan was OK and we ordered coffee. I appreciated that they heated up the milk, but the coffee was a little on the weak side for us.  All this for about $25, not a bad deal for lunch, couple that with great company and exceptional service, now that's what I call a winning combination!
